    • My chosen design and materials.
    • The door and mechanism is all mounted on the inside of the coop.
    • Door sliders made of wood, the door is a sloppy fit to ensure no binding.
    • 3D printed slider points 2 on each side take up the sloppy fit of the door.
    • The door is made from a piece of Aluminium checker plate 4mm thick.
    • The motor is a gearbox motor JGB37-520, 22RPM. . Do grease the gearbox as mine was dry
    • 3D printed motor mount
    • 31mm aluminium v groove pulley, giving the perfect speed opening and closing.
    • The door suspension can be easily be made from 70-80lb fishing line.
    • A fishing snood clip for easy disconnecting the door.
    • The large black object on the line is a cast piece of lead of 150g with a hole through the middle, 
this is in the event the door hits an object (chicken) the door can’t close any further, 
but the motor keeps going looking for the lower limit switch and unwinds the line until the motor timer kicks in
15 seconds, the weight keeps the line taught while this happens and then winds back up under tension to release 
the obstruction (safety release).
